    "body": "### Problem\n\nOn the home page, the two action buttons are too close together. When hovering over one button, it crashes with the neighboring button. Adding a little space between the buttons would enhance the look and feel of the page.\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/121039395/9fc0b0fa-e902-46da-b63d-3eb24cb950bb)\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/121039395/ee30e387-704b-42bd-b63a-5858bb0013e8)\r\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1.     Go to the home page.\r\n2.     Hover over one of the action buttons.\r\n3.     Observe that the button crashes with the neighboring button.\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThere should be a small gap between the two action buttons, so that they do not crash when hovering.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\ni don't know\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot applicable\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nnot applicable\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nnot applicable\n\n### Installation\n\nfrom source (using spack for convenience)",
